    "causal_summary": "sk-git's documented worktree convention is dir `.worktrees/{short-desc}` + branch `type/{short-desc}` (no number, no single grouping namespace), so feature worktrees were created ad-hoc as repo siblings that neither group in the Git UI nor sort in any stable order. Separately, the skill advisor routes git/worktree work to sk-git on **thin margins** (sk-git 0.85/0.16 vs system-spec-kit 0.82/0.22; sk-code-vs-sk-git ties), so git/worktree/branch/commit/PR intent does not reliably land on sk-git. This packet adopts branch `wt/{NNNN}-{name}` + dir `.worktrees/{NNNN}-{name}` for NAMED FEATURE worktrees (NNNN = max(existing)+1) and sharpens sk-git advisor triggers, scoping the ephemeral `worktree-session.sh` lane OUT.",
